\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. C. capitatus} Vandelli,{\i  Fasc. Pl.} 5 (1771) ({\i C. schoenoides} Griseb.,{\i  Galilea mucronata} (L.) Parl.). Perennial; roots lanate; rhizomes long, thick, with broad scales; stems 10-50 cm, solitary. Leaves 1-6 mm wide, with revolute margins. Bracts 3-6, with revolute margins, conspicuously dilated and often reddish at the base, exceeding the inflorescence. Inflorescence a dense, sessile, hemispherical to globose head. Spikelets 8-20 × 3-4 mm, lanceolate, with 8-12 flowers, patent. Rhachilla not winged. Glumes 5-8 × 2·5-4 mm, broadly lanceolate or ovate, obtuse but with a rigid mucro 1-3 mm, reddish or purplish, but yellowish-green in apical half, with a wide hyaline margin. Stamens 3. Nut c. 2/5 as long as glumes, brownish-yellow. 2n = 72. {\i Coastal sandy places. S. Europe}. Al Bl Bu Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si Tu.
\par

