\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. C. michelianus} (L.) Link,{\i  Hort. Berol. }{\b 1}: 303 (1827) ({\i Scirpus michelianus} L.). Caespitose annual; stems 1-28 cm. Leaves 0·5-2 mm wide, flat, shorter than to exceeding the stems. Bracts 3-8, dilated at the base, exceeding the inflorescence. Inflorescence a dense, sessile, ovoid to globose head. Spikelets 2-4 × 1-2 mm, lanceolate or oblong-lanceolate, with 8-20 flowers, patent. Rhachilla not winged. Glumes 1·2-2·5 × 0·5-0·6 mm, lanceolate, ovate-lanceolate or elliptical, acuminate, with an ascending to patent mucro 0·2-0·5 mm, hyaline or whitish-yellow, with greenish keel. Stamens 1-3. Nut 1/3-1/2 as long as the glumes, plano-convex or trigonous, pale brown.{\i  S. & C. Europe.} Au Bu Cz Ga Ge Gr †He Hu It Ju Lu Po Rm Rs (C, W, E).
\par

