\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 15. C. serotinus} Rottb., {\i Descr. Icon. Rar. Pl.} 31 (1773) ({\i Pycreus serotinus} (Rottb.) Hayek). Perennial; rhizomes long; stems 30-120 cm, solitary. Leaves 4-10 mm wide, subequalling to exceeding the stems. Bracts 3-5, exceeding the inflorescence. Inflorescence a compound umbel; rays 5-10, up to 15 cm. Spikelets 5-20(-30) × 2-3·5 mm, lanceolate or oblong-lanceolate, with 8-30 flowers, patent. Rhachilla not winged. Glumes 2-2·5 × 1·5-2 mm, broadly ovate to orbicular, obtuse, reddish-brown, with a greenish centre and a wide hyaline margin. Stamens 3. Nut ¾ as long as to subequalling the glumes, dark brown or black. {\i S. & E. Europe.} Al Au Bu Co Ga †He Hs Hu It Ju Lu Rm Rs (C, W, E) Tu.
