\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. C. pannonicus} Jacq.,{\i  Fl. Austr.}{\b  5}: 29 (1778) ({\i Acorellus pannonicus} (Jacq.) Palla). Caespitose, usually leafless annual or perennial; rhizomes very short; stems 1-40 cm; uppermost sheath sometimes with a lamina up to 5 cm × 1 mm. Bracts 2-3, conspicuously dilated at the base, the lower erect, forming an apparent prolongation of the stem, exceeding the inflorescence, the upper patent, shorter than to exceeding the inflorescence. Inflorescence a fascicle of 2-8 sessile spikelets. Spikelets 5-15 × 2-4 mm, broadly lanceolate or ovate, obtuse, with 10-40 flowers, ascending. Rhachilla not winged. Glumes 1·5-2 × 1·5-2·5 mm, ovate or suborbicular, obtuse, reddish or purplish-brown, with pale greenish stripe c. 1 mm wide in the centre. Stamens 3. Nut ¾ as long as to equalling the glumes, yellowish-brown.{\i  C. & S.E. Europe.} Al Au Bu Cz Hu Ju Rm Rs (C, W, K, E).
